                            <comment id="12889430" author="nspiegelberg" created="Sat, 17 Jul 2010 00:18:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For developer...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;psuedo-distributed ZK is more work than the others based upon the way that ZooKeeperWrapper &amp;amp; HQuorumPeer was written. Should still be doable, but noting some of the problems for consideration:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Need to add conf item (hbase.zookeeper.myid) to override ID lookup in HQuorumPeer.writeMyID()&lt;br/&gt;
2. These config params should be different per HQuorumPeer: hbase.zookeeper.property.clientPort + hbase.zookeeper.property.dataDir&lt;br/&gt;
3. hbase.zookeeper.property.server.&amp;lt;id&amp;gt; should be given to hbase as &amp;lt;addr&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;peer_port&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;leader_port&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;client_port&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
a. We currently don&apos;t allow a custom peer_port + leader_port even though ZK supports it&lt;br/&gt;
b. Need extra client_port for ZooKeeperWrapper.setQuorumServers()&lt;br/&gt;
4. GNU Parsing code needs to be added to HQuorumPeer to support overriding config values on the fly.  See HMaster.doMain() for help&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, make sure that the master rewrite code does not affect this change, if you finish first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12889431" author="nspiegelberg" created="Sat, 17 Jul 2010 00:21:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Code might need slight tweeks if master rewrite changes HQuorumPeer or ZooKeeperWrapper&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12889437" author="nspiegelberg" created="Sat, 17 Jul 2010 00:39:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also see: &lt;a href=&quot;http://hadoop.apache.org/zookeeper/docs/r3.3.0/zookeeperStarted.html#sc_RunningReplicatedZooKeeper&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hadoop.apache.org/zookeeper/docs/r3.3.0/zookeeperStarted.html#sc_RunningReplicatedZooKeeper&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14021365" author="apurtell" created="Sun, 8 Jun 2014 21:30:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stale issue. Reopen if still relevant. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lots of more current issues reworking our use of ZooKeeper, suggest moving relevant parts of this issue forward.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
